        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Doctor: expose sandbox registry findings",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Exposes legacy sandbox registry files as structured doctor health findings.\n- Adds dry-run repair effects for migrate, remove-empty, and quarantine registry-file outcomes.\n- Keeps the existing `doctor:sandbox` legacy run path as the only real mutating sandbox registry migration path for normal `doctor` / `doctor --fix`.\n- Declares the structured check inline on the existing ordered doctor contribution, so this PR does not add another core registry entry.\n- Aligns the structured check description and fix hint with the current SQLite sandbox registry contract.\n\nThis is intentionally the small sandbox registry slice from the doctor repair stack. It does not migrate sandbox image builds, namespace probes, Docker checks, or plugin-sensitive doctor rules.\n\n## Stack\n\nStacked on #86627. Current branch head is signed commit `a2b632a28846d7e8698e43c394a0dcec5853c9a7` (`fix(doctor): name sqlite sandbox registry repairs`).\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed:\nLegacy sandbox registry files are now visible through structured doctor health checks, while the existing `doctor --fix` path still owns the actual migration from legacy JSON/sharded registry files into SQLite-backed sandbox registry storage. Structured dry-run effects expose the intended migrate, quarantine, and remove-empty outcomes without mutating state.\n\nReal environment tested:\nWSL Ubuntu 24.04, OpenClaw checkout `/root/src/openclaw-84326-proof`, PR head `a2b632a28846d7e8698e43c394a0dcec5853c9a7`, source CLI via `node scripts/run-node.mjs`, source harness via `node --import tsx --input-type=module`, isolated temp `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`, temp `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH`, temp `HOME`, and synthetic legacy sandbox registry fixtures.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n1. Reused the prior isolated source CLI lint/fix proof for a valid legacy `sandbox/containers.json` migration into SQLite-backed `sandbox_registry_entries`.\n2. Ran a source harness importing `legacySandboxRegistryInspectionToHealthFinding` and `legacySandboxRegistryInspectionToRepairEffect` from `src/commands/doctor-sandbox.ts`.\n3. The harness emitted copied dry-run effect output for valid monolithic migrate, invalid monolithic quarantine, and empty sharded removal cases.\n4. Ran focused validation: `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/doctor-sandbox.warns-sandbox-enabled-without-docker.test.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts --reporter=dot`.\n5. Ran changed-file checks: targeted `oxlint`, targeted `oxfmt --check`, `git diff --check`, and `pnpm tsgo:core`.\n\nEvidence after fix:\nThe structured finding now points at SQLite, and dry-run repair effects cover all three registry-file outcomes:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"proof\": [\n    {\n      \"label\": \"migrate-valid-monolithic\",\n      \"checkId\": \"core/doctor/sandbox/registry-files\",\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"fixHint\": \"Run openclaw doctor --fix to migrate valid entries to SQLite.\",\n      \"message\": \"Legacy sandbox registry file detected.\\n- containers monolithic: <temp>/state/sandbox/containers.json (1 entry)\",\n      \"effect\": {\n        \"kind\": \"state\",\n        \"action\": \"would-migrate-legacy-sandbox-registry\",\n        \"target\": \"<temp>/state/sandbox/containers.json\",\n        \"dryRunSafe\": false\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"label\": \"quarantine-invalid-monolithic\",\n      \"checkId\": \"core/doctor/sandbox/registry-files\",\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"fixHint\": \"Run openclaw doctor --fix to migrate valid entries to SQLite.\",\n      \"message\": \"Legacy sandbox registry file detected.\\n- browsers monolithic: <temp>/state/sandbox/browsers.json (invalid)\",\n      \"effect\": {\n        \"kind\": \"state\",\n        \"action\": \"would-quarantine-legacy-sandbox-registry\",\n        \"target\": \"<temp>/state/sandbox/browsers.json\",\n        \"dryRunSafe\": false\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"label\": \"remove-empty-sharded\",\n      \"checkId\": \"core/doctor/sandbox/registry-files\",\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"fixHint\": \"Run openclaw doctor --fix to migrate valid entries to SQLite.\",\n      \"message\": \"Legacy sandbox registry file detected.\\n- containers sharded: <temp>/state/sandbox/containers (0 entries)\",\n      \"effect\": {\n        \"kind\": \"state\",\n        \"action\": \"would-remove-empty-legacy-sandbox-registry\",\n        \"target\": \"<temp>/state/sandbox/containers.json\",\n        \"dryRunSafe\": false\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nThe earlier real CLI fix proof still applies to the mutating path: `doctor --fix --yes --non-interactive` removed the legacy `containers.json`, printed the migration/doctor-complete markers, exited 0, and persisted the synthetic `openclaw-sbx-proof` row in SQLite `sandbox_registry_entries`.\n\nObserved result after fix:\nStructured sandbox registry findings and contribution metadata now describe SQLite-backed registry storage. The dry-run repair-effect path reports migrate, quarantine, and remove-empty effects without mutating state, while the real mutating path remains owned by `doctor --fix`.\n\nWhat was not tested:\nThe proof used synthetic legacy registry fixtures and did not run Docker, build sandbox images, probe namespaces, or exercise live sandbox container lifecycle. The prior `doctor --fix` source CLI run emitted an unrelated Gateway credentials warning while checking local Gateway status, but the command still exited 0 and the sandbox registry migration completed.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/doctor-sandbox.warns-sandbox-enabled-without-docker.test.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts --reporter=dot` -> 60 tests passed across 2 shards\n- `pnpm exec oxlint src/commands/doctor-sandbox.ts src/commands/doctor-sandbox.warns-sandbox-enabled-without-docker.test.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts` -> 0 warnings, 0 errors\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check src/commands/doctor-sandbox.ts src/commands/doctor-sandbox.warns-sandbox-enabled-without-docker.test.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`",
